Standard Bank’s Revenues to ‘Justify’ African Investments, Deputy CEO Says

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-03-15T10:48:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/standard-bank-s-revenues-to-justify-african-investments-deputy-ceo-says.html
Standard Bank Group Ltd.,  Africa ’s
largest bank, expects future revenues from its businesses across
the continent to justify its investment in infrastructure,
Deputy Chief Executive Officer Sim Tshabalala said.  The lender will “earn the right to expand internationally
only through achieving excellence in our home base,” he told
reporters in Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Renee Bonorchis in Johannesburg at 
 rbonorchis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
